# Grammar extensions beyond upstream (sqlglot v30.12.0) — the Class-A divergence ledger.
# One JSON object per line. Each row is a construct sqlglot-go parses STRUCTURALLY that pinned
# upstream does NOT (it falls back to exp.Command or raises). See DEVIATIONS.md "Grammar
# extensions beyond upstream" and AGENTS.md "How deviations are tracked".
#
# Fields:
#   id        — stable slug
#   dialect   — "" (base) | "mysql" | "postgres" | ...
#   sql       — a canonical example
#   upstream  — pinned-upstream behavior: "command" | "parse_error"
#   go_kind   — the root Kind class name sqlglot-go parses it to
#   reconcile — what to do if the pin-tripwire fires (upstream caught up)
#
# Enforced by extension_tripwire_test.go: TestUpstreamExtensionsGoSide (we parse it -> go_kind)
# and TestUpstreamExtensionsTripwire (pinned upstream still does `upstream`; fires at bump time).
{"id":"pg-explain","dialect":"postgres","sql":"EXPLAIN (ANALYZE, FORMAT JSON) SELECT a FROM t","upstream":"command","go_kind":"Describe","reconcile":"If upstream adds structural Postgres EXPLAIN, adopt its node shape (it will likely reuse exp.Describe) and delete this row + the Postgres EXPLAIN->DESCRIBE tokenizer alias / explain parser."}
